wt.eff

Class StandardEffService

  • java.lang.Object
    • wt.services.StandardManager
      • wt.eff.StandardEffService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, EffService

    public class StandardEffService
extends StandardManager
implements EffService, java.io.Serializable
    This standard implementation of EffService implements much extra functionality via listeners defined in performStartupProcess().

    In particular:

    • Delete
      • Delete the Effs of an EffManagedVersion when it is deleted
      • Veto EffContext deletion if its being referenced by existing Effs
      • Delete ProductInstances for an EffConfigItem when the configuration item is deleted
      • Remove an EffConfigItem's reference to a ProductSolution when the product solution is deleted
    • Check Out
      • Copy Effs from the original to the working copy
    • Check In
      • Replace original copy's Effs with the working copy's
    • Undo Check Out
      • Delete working copy's Effs
    • Add/Replace Effs Using EffGroupAssistant
      • Veto assignment of Incorporation Date for a ProductInstance that has either not been built or that was built after the assigned incorporation date.

    Use the newStandardEffService static factory method(s), not the StandardEffService constructor, to construct instances of this class. Instances must be constructed using the static factory(s), in order to ensure proper initialization of the instance.



    Supported API: true

    Extendable: false
